title: For Sale:  US GI Unit Match Pistol 1911
postcontent: This pistol was likely built at the unit level, rather than anarmory somewhere ( no armory markings ) It  contains National Match GI slide, sights, barrel, bushing. And,  as so many were, this pistol was built on a commercial frame. ( I don't know who made this frame as it only appears to have a National Match serial number.) Commercial frames were used so the pistol actually belonged to the shooter, and not to the Government. It could go with the shooter to his next duty station. This pistol was ( I believe ) built for HARDBALL pistol matches. Also called Service Pistol Matches. I would have a > 4lb trigger. It is marked AF on the right leg of the barrel, so it was likely an Air Force unit pistol. The frame to slide fit is very tight and the bushing requires a bushing wrench to be removed. This pistol was made to " hit what you are aimong at ". Notice the polished pins on the right side of the pistol....that's about as fancy as they made them...  Parkerized finish shows a little thinning on the front strap.
